= SDL_GetKeyName =
Use this function to get a human-readable name for a key.


== Syntax ==
```c++
const char* SDL_GetKeyName(SDLKey key)
```

== Function Parameters ==
{|
|'''key'''
|the desired SDLKey to query ???
|}

== Return Value ==
A pointer to a UTF-8 string that stays valid at least until the next call to this function. If you need it around any longer, you must copy it. If the key doesn't have a name, this function returns an empty string ("").  <<Color2(green,Should key here be bold?)>>

